The United States changes the rules for obtaining a visa 
The people must stand before their conversation in the consulate in the service of applying for a visa; costs will be waiting times shortened. 
From 10 January 2011 change The procedure for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and the consulates. 
In the new procedure must most applicants before their conversation at the consulate in the service of applying for a visa (ASC beginning letters in English). 
The staff of the ASC adopted the biometric data of the petitioner at the consulate be reviewed before the conversation. 
The new procedure has certain advantages for the Aspiranten, include: 
The total cost for the implementation of the visa drop, because it is no longer needed the date of arrangement, the processing of visa applications and the transport service with which the document is handed to pay separately. 
The author makes only a single payment, which covers the three services. 
The current price remains unchanged: The Gegenwerit to $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas with request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for Händer and investors. 
Those who wish to extend their visa only must not lead at the consulate, they need only imagine the nearest ASC, where they present their documents and their fingerprints will be taken. 
Because the ASC biometric data is being collected, remain the applicants who need a second deadline for the talks at the consulate, there is less time than before. 
The visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo, need not pay the service charge of $26. 
